74bool SendPeriodicFeedback(const std::vector<RtpExtension>& extensions) {
75 for (const auto& extension : extensions) {
76 if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberV2Uri)
77 return false;
78 }
79 return true;
80}
81
82// TODO(nisse): This really begs for a shared context struct.
83bool UseSendSideBwe(const std::vector<RtpExtension>& extensions,
84 bool transport_cc) {
85 if (!transport_cc)
86 return false;
87 for (const auto& extension : extensions) {
88 if (extension.uri == RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberUri ||
89 extension.uri == RtpExtension::kTransportSequenceNumberV2Uri)
90 return true;
91 }
92 return false;
93}
94
95bool UseSendSideBwe(const VideoReceiveStream::Config& config) {
96 return UseSendSideBwe(config.rtp.extensions, config.rtp.transport_cc);
97}
98
99bool UseSendSideBwe(const AudioReceiveStream::Config& config) {
100 return UseSendSideBwe(config.rtp.extensions, config.rtp.transport_cc);
101}
102
103bool UseSendSideBwe(const FlexfecReceiveStream::Config& config) {
104 return UseSendSideBwe(config.rtp_header_extensions, config.transport_cc);
105}

107const int* FindKeyByValue(const std::map<int, int>& m, int v) {
108 for (const auto& kv : m) {
109 if (kv.second == v)
110 return &kv.first;
111 }
112 return nullptr;
113}

115std::unique_ptr<rtclog::StreamConfig> CreateRtcLogStreamConfig(
116 const VideoReceiveStream::Config& config) {
117 auto rtclog_config = std::make_unique<rtclog::StreamConfig>();
118 rtclog_config->remote_ssrc = config.rtp.remote_ssrc;
119 rtclog_config->local_ssrc = config.rtp.local_ssrc;
120 rtclog_config->rtx_ssrc = config.rtp.rtx_ssrc;
121 rtclog_config->rtcp_mode = config.rtp.rtcp_mode;
122 rtclog_config->rtp_extensions = config.rtp.extensions;
123
124 for (const auto& d : config.decoders) {
125 const int* search =
126 FindKeyByValue(config.rtp.rtx_associated_payload_types, d.payload_type);
127 rtclog_config->codecs.emplace_back(d.video_format.name, d.payload_type,
128 search ? *search : 0);
129 }
130 return rtclog_config;
131}

133std::unique_ptr<rtclog::StreamConfig> CreateRtcLogStreamConfig(
134 const VideoSendStream::Config& config,
135 size_t ssrc_index) {
136 auto rtclog_config = std::make_unique<rtclog::StreamConfig>();
137 rtclog_config->local_ssrc = config.rtp.ssrcs[ssrc_index];
138 if (ssrc_index < config.rtp.rtx.ssrcs.size()) {
139 rtclog_config->rtx_ssrc = config.rtp.rtx.ssrcs[ssrc_index];
140 }
141 rtclog_config->rtcp_mode = config.rtp.rtcp_mode;
142 rtclog_config->rtp_extensions = config.rtp.extensions;
143
144 rtclog_config->codecs.emplace_back(config.rtp.payload_name,
145 config.rtp.payload_type,
146 config.rtp.rtx.payload_type);
147 return rtclog_config;
148}

171// Called from the destructor of Call to report the collected send histograms.
172void UpdateSendHistograms(Timestamp now,
173 Timestamp first_sent_packet,
174 AvgCounter& estimated_send_bitrate_kbps_counter,
175 AvgCounter& pacer_bitrate_kbps_counter) {
176 TimeDelta elapsed = now - first_sent_packet;
177 if (elapsed.seconds() < metrics::kMinRunTimeInSeconds)
178 return;
179
180 const int kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples = 5;
181 AggregatedStats send_bitrate_stats =
182 estimated_send_bitrate_kbps_counter.ProcessAndGetStats();
183 if (send_bitrate_stats.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
184 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.EstimatedSendBitrateInKbps",
185 send_bitrate_stats.average);
186 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRTC.Call.EstimatedSendBitrateInKbps, "
187 << send_bitrate_stats.ToString();
188 }
189 AggregatedStats pacer_bitrate_stats =
190 pacer_bitrate_kbps_counter.ProcessAndGetStats();
191 if (pacer_bitrate_stats.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
192 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.PacerBitrateInKbps",
193 pacer_bitrate_stats.average);
194 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRTC.Call.PacerBitrateInKbps, "
195 << pacer_bitrate_stats.ToString();
196 }
197}

203// Wraps an injected resource in a BroadcastResourceListener and handles adding
204// and removing adapter resources to individual VideoSendStreams.
205class ResourceVideoSendStreamForwarder {
206 public:
207 ResourceVideoSendStreamForwarder(
208 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::Resource> resource)
209 : broadcast_resource_listener_(resource) {
210 broadcast_resource_listener_.StartListening();
211 }
212 ~ResourceVideoSendStreamForwarder() {
213 RTC_DCHECK(adapter_resources_.empty());
214 broadcast_resource_listener_.StopListening();
215 }
216
217 rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::Resource> Resource() const {
218 return broadcast_resource_listener_.SourceResource();
219 }
220
221 void OnCreateVideoSendStream(VideoSendStream* video_send_stream) {
222 RTC_DCHECK(adapter_resources_.find(video_send_stream) ==
223 adapter_resources_.end());
224 auto adapter_resource =
225 broadcast_resource_listener_.CreateAdapterResource();
226 video_send_stream->AddAdaptationResource(adapter_resource);
227 adapter_resources_.insert(
228 std::make_pair(video_send_stream, adapter_resource));
229 }
230
231 void OnDestroyVideoSendStream(VideoSendStream* video_send_stream) {
232 auto it = adapter_resources_.find(video_send_stream);
233 RTC_DCHECK(it != adapter_resources_.end());
234 broadcast_resource_listener_.RemoveAdapterResource(it->second);
235 adapter_resources_.erase(it);
236 }
237
238 private:
239 BroadcastResourceListener broadcast_resource_listener_;
240 std::map<VideoSendStream*, rtc::scoped_refptr<webrtc::Resource>>
241 adapter_resources_;
242};

488std::string Call::Stats::ToString(int64_t time_ms) const {

490 rtc::SimpleStringBuilder ss(buf);

528class SharedModuleThread::Impl {
529 public:
530 Impl(std::unique_ptr<ProcessThread> process_thread,
531 std::function<void()> on_one_ref_remaining)
532 : module_thread_(std::move(process_thread)),
533 on_one_ref_remaining_(std::move(on_one_ref_remaining)) {}
534
535 void EnsureStarted() {
536 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
537 if (started_)
538 return;
539 started_ = true;
540 module_thread_->Start();
541 }
542
543 ProcessThread* process_thread() {
544 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
545 return module_thread_.get();
546 }
547
548 void AddRef() const {
549 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
550 ++ref_count_;
551 }
552
553 rtc::RefCountReleaseStatus Release() const {
554 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(&sequence_checker_);
555 --ref_count_;
556
557 if (ref_count_ == 0) {
558 module_thread_->Stop();
559 return rtc::RefCountReleaseStatus::kDroppedLastRef;
560 }
561
562 if (ref_count_ == 1 && on_one_ref_remaining_) {
563 auto moved_fn = std::move(on_one_ref_remaining_);
564 // NOTE: after this function returns, chances are that |this| has been
565 // deleted - do not touch any member variables.
566 // If the owner of the last reference implements a lambda that releases
567 // that last reference inside of the callback (which is legal according
568 // to this implementation), we will recursively enter Release() above,
569 // call Stop() and release the last reference.
570 moved_fn();
571 }
572
573 return rtc::RefCountReleaseStatus::kOtherRefsRemained;
574 }
575
576 private:
577 RTC_NO_UNIQUE_ADDRESS SequenceChecker sequence_checker_;
578 mutable int ref_count_ RTC_GUARDED_BY(sequence_checker_) = 0;
579 std::unique_ptr<ProcessThread> const module_thread_;
580 std::function<void()> const on_one_ref_remaining_;
581 bool started_ = false;
582};
583
584SharedModuleThread::SharedModuleThread(
585 std::unique_ptr<ProcessThread> process_thread,
586 std::function<void()> on_one_ref_remaining)
587 : impl_(std::make_unique<Impl>(std::move(process_thread),
588 std::move(on_one_ref_remaining))) {}
589
590SharedModuleThread::~SharedModuleThread() = default;

690Call::~Call() {
691 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
692
693 RTC_CHECK(audio_send_ssrcs_.empty());
694 RTC_CHECK(video_send_ssrcs_.empty());
695 RTC_CHECK(video_send_streams_.empty());
696 RTC_CHECK(audio_receive_streams_.empty());
697 RTC_CHECK(video_receive_streams_.empty());
698
699 module_process_thread_->process_thread()->DeRegisterModule(
700 receive_side_cc_.GetRemoteBitrateEstimator(true));
701 module_process_thread_->process_thread()->DeRegisterModule(&receive_side_cc_);
702 call_stats_->DeregisterStatsObserver(&receive_side_cc_);
703
704 absl::optional<Timestamp> first_sent_packet_time =
705 transport_send_->GetFirstPacketTime();
706
707 Timestamp now = clock_->CurrentTime();
708
709 // Only update histograms after process threads have been shut down, so that
710 // they won't try to concurrently update stats.
711 if (first_sent_packet_time) {
712 UpdateSendHistograms(now, *first_sent_packet_time,
713 estimated_send_bitrate_kbps_counter_,
714 pacer_bitrate_kbps_counter_);
715 }
716
717 UpdateReceiveHistograms();
718
719 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.LifetimeInSeconds",
720 (now.ms() - start_ms_) / 1000);
721}

744void Call::UpdateReceiveHistograms() {
745 if (first_received_rtp_audio_ms_) {
746 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000(
747 "WebRTC.Call.TimeReceivingAudioRtpPacketsInSeconds",
748 (*last_received_rtp_audio_ms_ - *first_received_rtp_audio_ms_) / 1000);
749 }
750 if (first_received_rtp_video_ms_) {
751 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000(
752 "WebRTC.Call.TimeReceivingVideoRtpPacketsInSeconds",
753 (*last_received_rtp_video_ms_ - *first_received_rtp_video_ms_) / 1000);
754 }
755 const int kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples = 5;
756 AggregatedStats video_bytes_per_sec =
757 received_video_bytes_per_second_counter_.GetStats();
758 if (video_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
759 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.VideoBitrateReceivedInKbps",
760 video_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
761 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRTC.Call.VideoBitrateReceivedInBps, "
762 << video_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8);
763 }
764 AggregatedStats audio_bytes_per_sec =
765 received_audio_bytes_per_second_counter_.GetStats();
766 if (audio_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
767 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.AudioBitrateReceivedInKbps",
768 audio_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
769 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRTC.Call.AudioBitrateReceivedInBps, "
770 << audio_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8);
771 }
772 AggregatedStats rtcp_bytes_per_sec =
773 received_rtcp_bytes_per_second_counter_.GetStats();
774 if (rtcp_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
775 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.RtcpBitrateReceivedInBps",
776 rtcp_bytes_per_sec.average * 8);
777 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRTC.Call.RtcpBitrateReceivedInBps, "
778 << rtcp_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8);
779 }
780 AggregatedStats recv_bytes_per_sec =
781 received_bytes_per_second_counter_.GetStats();
782 if (recv_bytes_per_sec.num_samples > kMinRequiredPeriodicSamples) {
783 RTC_HISTOGRAM_COUNTS_100000("WebRTC.Call.BitrateReceivedInKbps",
784 recv_bytes_per_sec.average * 8 / 1000);
785 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "WebRTC.Call.BitrateReceivedInBps, "
786 << recv_bytes_per_sec.ToStringWithMultiplier(8);
787 }

794webrtc::AudioSendStream* Call::CreateAudioSendStream(
795 const webrtc::AudioSendStream::Config& config) {
796 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "Call::CreateAudioSendStream");
797 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
798
799 EnsureStarted();
800
801 // Stream config is logged in AudioSendStream::ConfigureStream, as it may
802 // change during the stream's lifetime.
803 absl::optional<RtpState> suspended_rtp_state;
804 {
805 const auto& iter = suspended_audio_send_ssrcs_.find(config.rtp.ssrc);
806 if (iter != suspended_audio_send_ssrcs_.end()) {
807 suspended_rtp_state.emplace(iter->second);
808 }
809 }
810
811 AudioSendStream* send_stream = new AudioSendStream(
812 clock_, config, config_.audio_state, task_queue_factory_,
813 module_process_thread_->process_thread(), transport_send_ptr_,
814 bitrate_allocator_.get(), event_log_, call_stats_->AsRtcpRttStats(),
815 suspended_rtp_state);
816 RTC_DCHECK(audio_send_ssrcs_.find(config.rtp.ssrc) ==
817 audio_send_ssrcs_.end());
818 audio_send_ssrcs_[config.rtp.ssrc] = send_stream;
819
820 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): call AssociateSendStream and
821 // UpdateAggregateNetworkState asynchronously on the network thread.
822 for (AudioReceiveStream* stream : audio_receive_streams_) {
823 if (stream->config().rtp.local_ssrc == config.rtp.ssrc) {
824 stream->AssociateSendStream(send_stream);
825 }
826 }
827
828 UpdateAggregateNetworkState();
829
830 return send_stream;
831}

834 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "Call::DestroyAudioSendStream");
835 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);

837
838 send_stream->Stop();
839
840 const uint32_t ssrc = send_stream->GetConfig().rtp.ssrc;

843 suspended_audio_send_ssrcs_[ssrc] = audio_send_stream->GetRtpState();
844
845 size_t num_deleted = audio_send_ssrcs_.erase(ssrc);
846 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(1, num_deleted);
847
848 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): call AssociateSendStream and
849 // UpdateAggregateNetworkState asynchronously on the network thread.
850 for (AudioReceiveStream* stream : audio_receive_streams_) {
851 if (stream->config().rtp.local_ssrc == ssrc) {
852 stream->AssociateSendStream(nullptr);
853 }
854 }
855
856 UpdateAggregateNetworkState();
857
858 delete send_stream;

866 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventAudioReceiveStreamConfig>(

868

918 receive_rtp_config_.erase(ssrc);
919
920 UpdateAggregateNetworkState();
921 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Consider if deleting |audio_receive_stream|
922 // on the network thread would be better or if we'd need to tear down the
923 // state in two phases.
924 delete audio_receive_stream;

935 EnsureStarted();

937 video_send_delay_stats_->AddSsrcs(config);

985void Call::DestroyVideoSendStream(webrtc::VideoSendStream* send_stream) {
986 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "Call::DestroyVideoSendStream");
987 RTC_DCHECK(send_stream != nullptr);
988 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
989
990 send_stream->Stop();
991
992 VideoSendStream* send_stream_impl = nullptr;
993
994 auto it = video_send_ssrcs_.begin();
995 while (it != video_send_ssrcs_.end()) {
996 if (it->second == static_cast<VideoSendStream*>(send_stream)) {
997 send_stream_impl = it->second;
998 video_send_ssrcs_.erase(it++);
999 } else {
1000 ++it;
1001 }
1002 }
1003 // Stop forwarding resources to the stream being destroyed.
1004 for (const auto& resource_forwarder : adaptation_resource_forwarders_) {
1005 resource_forwarder->OnDestroyVideoSendStream(send_stream_impl);
1006 }
1007 video_send_streams_.erase(send_stream_impl);
1008
1009 RTC_CHECK(send_stream_impl != nullptr);
1010
1011 VideoSendStream::RtpStateMap rtp_states;
1012 VideoSendStream::RtpPayloadStateMap rtp_payload_states;
1013 send_stream_impl->StopPermanentlyAndGetRtpStates(&rtp_states,
1014 &rtp_payload_states);
1015 for (const auto& kv : rtp_states) {
1016 suspended_video_send_ssrcs_[kv.first] = kv.second;
1017 }
1018 for (const auto& kv : rtp_payload_states) {
1019 suspended_video_payload_states_[kv.first] = kv.second;
1020 }
1021
1022 UpdateAggregateNetworkState();
1023 delete send_stream_impl;
1024}

1026webrtc::VideoReceiveStream* Call::CreateVideoReceiveStream(
1027 webrtc::VideoReceiveStream::Config configuration) {
1028 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "Call::CreateVideoReceiveStream");
1029 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1030
1031 receive_side_cc_.SetSendPeriodicFeedback(
1032 SendPeriodicFeedback(configuration.rtp.extensions));
1033
1034 EnsureStarted();
1035
1036 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Move the registration between |receive_stream|
1037 // and |video_receiver_controller_| out of VideoReceiveStream2 construction
1038 // and set it up asynchronously on the network thread (the registration and
1039 // |video_receiver_controller_| need to live on the network thread).
1040 VideoReceiveStream2* receive_stream = new VideoReceiveStream2(

1047 if (config.rtp.rtx_ssrc) {

1049 // stream. Since the transport_send_cc negotiation is per payload
1050 // type, we may get an incorrect value for the rtx stream, but
1051 // that is unlikely to matter in practice.
1052 receive_rtp_config_.emplace(config.rtp.rtx_ssrc, ReceiveRtpConfig(config));
1053 }
1054 receive_rtp_config_.emplace(config.rtp.remote_ssrc, ReceiveRtpConfig(config));

1184void Call::SignalChannelNetworkState(MediaType media, NetworkState state) {
1185 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1186 RTC_DCHECK(media == MediaType::AUDIO || media == MediaType::VIDEO);
1187
1188 auto closure = [this, media, state]() {
1189 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Move this over to the network thread.
1190 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1191 if (media == MediaType::AUDIO) {
1192 audio_network_state_ = state;
1193 } else {
1194 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media, MediaType::VIDEO);
1195 video_network_state_ = state;
1196 }
1197
1198 // TODO(tommi): Is it necessary to always do this, including if there
1199 // was no change in state?
1200 UpdateAggregateNetworkState();
1201
1202 // TODO(tommi): Is it right to do this if media == AUDIO?
1203 for (VideoReceiveStream2* video_receive_stream : video_receive_streams_) {
1204 video_receive_stream->SignalNetworkState(video_network_state_);
1205 }
1206 };
1207
1208 if (network_thread_ == worker_thread_) {
1209 closure();
1210 } else {
1211 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Remove workaround when we no longer need to
1212 // post to the worker thread.
1213 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(task_safety_, std::move(closure)));
1214 }
1215}

1229void Call::UpdateAggregateNetworkState() {
1230 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Move this over to the network thread.
1231 // RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1232
1233 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1234
1235 bool have_audio =
1236 !audio_send_ssrcs_.empty() || !audio_receive_streams_.empty();
1237 bool have_video =
1238 !video_send_ssrcs_.empty() || !video_receive_streams_.empty();
1239
1240 bool aggregate_network_up =
1241 ((have_video && video_network_state_ == kNetworkUp) ||
1242 (have_audio && audio_network_state_ == kNetworkUp));
1243
1244 if (aggregate_network_up != aggregate_network_up_) {
1245 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
1246 << "UpdateAggregateNetworkState: aggregate_state change to "
1247 << (aggregate_network_up ? "up" : "down");
1248 } else {
1249 RTC_LOG(LS_VERBOSE)
1250 << "UpdateAggregateNetworkState: aggregate_state remains at "
1251 << (aggregate_network_up ? "up" : "down");
1252 }
1253 aggregate_network_up_ = aggregate_network_up;
1254
1255 transport_send_ptr_->OnNetworkAvailability(aggregate_network_up);
1256}

1275void Call::OnTargetTransferRate(TargetTransferRate msg) {

1277
1278 uint32_t target_bitrate_bps = msg.target_rate.bps();
1279 // For controlling the rate of feedback messages.
1280 receive_side_cc_.OnBitrateChanged(target_bitrate_bps);
1281 bitrate_allocator_->OnNetworkEstimateChanged(msg);

1289 // down) or if we're not sending video.

1291 estimated_send_bitrate_kbps_counter_.ProcessAndPause();

1300 std::max(target_bitrate_bps, min_allocated_send_bitrate_bps_);
1301 pacer_bitrate_kbps_counter_.Add(pacer_bitrate_bps / 1000);
1302 }));

1317void Call::ConfigureSync(const std::string& sync_group) {
1318 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Expect to be called on the network thread.
1319 // Set sync only if there was no previous one.
1320 if (sync_group.empty())
1321 return;
1322
1323 AudioReceiveStream* sync_audio_stream = nullptr;
1324 // Find existing audio stream.
1325 const auto it = sync_stream_mapping_.find(sync_group);
1326 if (it != sync_stream_mapping_.end()) {
1327 sync_audio_stream = it->second;
1328 } else {
1329 // No configured audio stream, see if we can find one.
1330 for (AudioReceiveStream* stream : audio_receive_streams_) {
1331 if (stream->config().sync_group == sync_group) {
1332 if (sync_audio_stream != nullptr) {
1333 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1334 << "Attempting to sync more than one audio stream "
1335 "within the same sync group. This is not "
1336 "supported in the current implementation.";
1337 break;
1338 }
1339 sync_audio_stream = stream;
1340 }
1341 }
1342 }
1343 if (sync_audio_stream)
1344 sync_stream_mapping_[sync_group] = sync_audio_stream;
1345 size_t num_synced_streams = 0;
1346 for (VideoReceiveStream2* video_stream : video_receive_streams_) {
1347 if (video_stream->config().sync_group != sync_group)
1348 continue;
1349 ++num_synced_streams;
1350 if (num_synced_streams > 1) {
1351 // TODO(pbos): Support synchronizing more than one A/V pair.
1352 // https://code.google.com/p/webrtc/issues/detail?id=4762
1353 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
1354 << "Attempting to sync more than one audio/video pair "
1355 "within the same sync group. This is not supported in "
1356 "the current implementation.";
1357 }
1358 // Only sync the first A/V pair within this sync group.
1359 if (num_synced_streams == 1) {
1360 // sync_audio_stream may be null and that's ok.
1361 video_stream->SetSync(sync_audio_stream);
1362 } else {
1363 video_stream->SetSync(nullptr);
1364 }
1365 }
1366}

1368PacketReceiver::DeliveryStatus Call::DeliverRtcp(MediaType media_type,
1369 const uint8_t* packet,
1370 size_t length) {
1371 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "Call::DeliverRtcp");
1372
1373 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): This DCHECK is here just to maintain the
1374 // invariant that currently the only call path to this function is via
1375 // `PeerConnection::InitializeRtcpCallback()`. DeliverRtp on the other hand
1376 // gets called via the channel classes and
1377 // WebRtc[Audio|Video]Channel's `OnPacketReceived`. We'll remove the
1378 // PeerConnection involvement as well as
1379 // `JsepTransportController::OnRtcpPacketReceived_n` and `rtcp_handler`
1380 // and make sure that the flow of packets is consistent from the
1381 // `RtpTransport` class, via the *Channel and *Engine classes and into Call.
1382 // This way we'll also know more about the context of the packet.
1383 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(media_type, MediaType::ANY);
1384
1385 // TODO(pbos): Make sure it's a valid packet.
1386 // Return DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC if it can be determined that
1387 // there's no receiver of the packet.
1388 if (received_bytes_per_second_counter_.HasSample()) {
1389 // First RTP packet has been received.
1390 received_bytes_per_second_counter_.Add(static_cast<int>(length));
1391 received_rtcp_bytes_per_second_counter_.Add(static_cast<int>(length));
1392 }
1393 bool rtcp_delivered = false;
1394 if (media_type == MediaType::ANY || media_type == MediaType::VIDEO) {
1395 for (VideoReceiveStream2* stream : video_receive_streams_) {
1396 if (stream->DeliverRtcp(packet, length))
1397 rtcp_delivered = true;
1398 }
1399 }
1400 if (media_type == MediaType::ANY || media_type == MediaType::AUDIO) {
1401 for (AudioReceiveStream* stream : audio_receive_streams_) {
1402 stream->DeliverRtcp(packet, length);
1403 rtcp_delivered = true;
1404 }
1405 }
1406 if (media_type == MediaType::ANY || media_type == MediaType::VIDEO) {
1407 for (VideoSendStream* stream : video_send_streams_) {
1408 stream->DeliverRtcp(packet, length);
1409 rtcp_delivered = true;
1410 }
1411 }
1412 if (media_type == MediaType::ANY || media_type == MediaType::AUDIO) {
1413 for (auto& kv : audio_send_ssrcs_) {
1414 kv.second->DeliverRtcp(packet, length);
1415 rtcp_delivered = true;
1416 }
1417 }
1418
1419 if (rtcp_delivered) {
1420 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventRtcpPacketIncoming>(
1421 rtc::MakeArrayView(packet, length)));
1422 }
1423
1424 return rtcp_delivered ? DELIVERY_OK : DELIVERY_PACKET_ERROR;
1425}
1426
1427PacketReceiver::DeliveryStatus Call::DeliverRtp(MediaType media_type,
1428 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet,
1429 int64_t packet_time_us) {
1430 TRACE_EVENT0("webrtc", "Call::DeliverRtp");
1431 RTC_DCHECK_NE(media_type, MediaType::ANY);
1432
1433 RtpPacketReceived parsed_packet;
1434 if (!parsed_packet.Parse(std::move(packet)))
1435 return DELIVERY_PACKET_ERROR;
1436
1437 if (packet_time_us != -1) {
1438 if (receive_time_calculator_) {
1439 // Repair packet_time_us for clock resets by comparing a new read of
1440 // the same clock (TimeUTCMicros) to a monotonic clock reading.
1441 packet_time_us = receive_time_calculator_->ReconcileReceiveTimes(
1442 packet_time_us, rtc::TimeUTCMicros(), clock_->TimeInMicroseconds());
1443 }
1444 parsed_packet.set_arrival_time(Timestamp::Micros(packet_time_us));
1445 } else {
1446 parsed_packet.set_arrival_time(clock_->CurrentTime());
1447 }
1448
1449 // We might get RTP keep-alive packets in accordance with RFC6263 section 4.6.
1450 // These are empty (zero length payload) RTP packets with an unsignaled
1451 // payload type.
1452 const bool is_keep_alive_packet = parsed_packet.payload_size() == 0;
1453
1454 RTC_DCHECK(media_type == MediaType::AUDIO || media_type == MediaType::VIDEO ||
1455 is_keep_alive_packet);
1456
1457 auto it = receive_rtp_config_.find(parsed_packet.Ssrc());
1458 if (it == receive_rtp_config_.end()) {
1459 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "receive_rtp_config_ lookup failed for ssrc "
1460 << parsed_packet.Ssrc();
1461 // Destruction of the receive stream, including deregistering from the
1462 // RtpDemuxer, is not protected by the |worker_thread_|.
1463 // But deregistering in the |receive_rtp_config_| map is. So by not passing
1464 // the packet on to demuxing in this case, we prevent incoming packets to be
1465 // passed on via the demuxer to a receive stream which is being torned down.
1466 return DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC;
1467 }
1468
1469 parsed_packet.IdentifyExtensions(it->second.extensions);
1470
1471 NotifyBweOfReceivedPacket(parsed_packet, media_type);
1472
1473 // RateCounters expect input parameter as int, save it as int,
1474 // instead of converting each time it is passed to RateCounter::Add below.
1475 int length = static_cast<int>(parsed_packet.size());
1476 if (media_type == MediaType::AUDIO) {
1477 if (audio_receiver_controller_.OnRtpPacket(parsed_packet)) {
1478 received_bytes_per_second_counter_.Add(length);
1479 received_audio_bytes_per_second_counter_.Add(length);
1480 event_log_->Log(
1481 std::make_unique<RtcEventRtpPacketIncoming>(parsed_packet));
1482 const int64_t arrival_time_ms = parsed_packet.arrival_time().ms();
1483 if (!first_received_rtp_audio_ms_) {
1484 first_received_rtp_audio_ms_.emplace(arrival_time_ms);
1485 }
1486 last_received_rtp_audio_ms_.emplace(arrival_time_ms);
1487 return DELIVERY_OK;
1488 }
1489 } else if (media_type == MediaType::VIDEO) {
1490 parsed_packet.set_payload_type_frequency(kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency);
1491 if (video_receiver_controller_.OnRtpPacket(parsed_packet)) {
1492 received_bytes_per_second_counter_.Add(length);
1493 received_video_bytes_per_second_counter_.Add(length);
1494 event_log_->Log(
1495 std::make_unique<RtcEventRtpPacketIncoming>(parsed_packet));
1496 const int64_t arrival_time_ms = parsed_packet.arrival_time().ms();
1497 if (!first_received_rtp_video_ms_) {
1498 first_received_rtp_video_ms_.emplace(arrival_time_ms);
1499 }
1500 last_received_rtp_video_ms_.emplace(arrival_time_ms);
1501 return DELIVERY_OK;
1502 }
1503 }
1504 return DELIVERY_UNKNOWN_SSRC;
1505}

1508 MediaType media_type,
1509 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet,
1510 int64_t packet_time_us) {
1511 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1512
1513 if (IsRtcp(packet.cdata(), packet.size()))
1514 return DeliverRtcp(media_type, packet.cdata(), packet.size());
1515

1519void Call::DeliverPacketAsync(MediaType media_type,
1520 rtc::CopyOnWriteBuffer packet,
1521 int64_t packet_time_us,
1522 PacketCallback callback) {
1523 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(network_thread_);
1524
1525 TaskQueueBase* network_thread = rtc::Thread::Current();
1526 RTC_DCHECK(network_thread);
1527
1528 worker_thread_->PostTask(ToQueuedTask(
1529 task_safety_, [this, network_thread, media_type, p = std::move(packet),

1535 ToQueuedTask([cb = std::move(cb), status, media_type,
1536 p = std::move(p), packet_time_us]() {
1537 cb(status, media_type, std::move(p), packet_time_us);

1543void Call::OnRecoveredPacket(const uint8_t* packet, size_t length) {
1544 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/11993): Expect to be called on the network thread.
1545 // This method is called synchronously via |OnRtpPacket()| (see DeliverRtp)
1546 // on the same thread.
1547 RTC_DCHECK_RUN_ON(worker_thread_);
1548 RtpPacketReceived parsed_packet;
1549 if (!parsed_packet.Parse(packet, length))
1550 return;
1551
1552 parsed_packet.set_recovered(true);
1553
1554 auto it = receive_rtp_config_.find(parsed_packet.Ssrc());
1555 if (it == receive_rtp_config_.end()) {
1556 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "receive_rtp_config_ lookup failed for ssrc "
1557 << parsed_packet.Ssrc();
1558 // Destruction of the receive stream, including deregistering from the
1559 // RtpDemuxer, is not protected by the |worker_thread_|.
1560 // But deregistering in the |receive_rtp_config_| map is.
1561 // So by not passing the packet on to demuxing in this case, we prevent
1562 // incoming packets to be passed on via the demuxer to a receive stream
1563 // which is being torn down.
1564 return;
1565 }
1566 parsed_packet.IdentifyExtensions(it->second.extensions);
1567
1568 // TODO(brandtr): Update here when we support protecting audio packets too.
1569 parsed_packet.set_payload_type_frequency(kVideoPayloadTypeFrequency);
1570 video_receiver_controller_.OnRtpPacket(parsed_packet);
1571}
1572
1573void Call::NotifyBweOfReceivedPacket(const RtpPacketReceived& packet,
1574 MediaType media_type) {
1575 auto it = receive_rtp_config_.find(packet.Ssrc());
1576 bool use_send_side_bwe =
1577 (it != receive_rtp_config_.end()) && it->second.use_send_side_bwe;
1578
1579 RTPHeader header;
1580 packet.GetHeader(&header);
1581
1582 ReceivedPacket packet_msg;
1583 packet_msg.size = DataSize::Bytes(packet.payload_size());
1584 packet_msg.receive_time = packet.arrival_time();
1585 if (header.extension.hasAbsoluteSendTime) {
1586 packet_msg.send_time = header.extension.GetAbsoluteSendTimestamp();
1587 }
1588 transport_send_ptr_->OnReceivedPacket(packet_msg);
1589
1590 if (!use_send_side_bwe && header.extension.hasTransportSequenceNumber) {
1591 // Inconsistent configuration of send side BWE. Do nothing.
1592 // TODO(nisse): Without this check, we may produce RTCP feedback
1593 // packets even when not negotiated. But it would be cleaner to
1594 // move the check down to RTCPSender::SendFeedbackPacket, which
1595 // would also help the PacketRouter to select an appropriate rtp
1596 // module in the case that some, but not all, have RTCP feedback
1597 // enabled.
1598 return;
1599 }
1600 // For audio, we only support send side BWE.
1601 if (media_type == MediaType::VIDEO ||
1602 (use_send_side_bwe && header.extension.hasTransportSequenceNumber)) {
1603 receive_side_cc_.OnReceivedPacket(
1604 packet.arrival_time().ms(),
1605 packet.payload_size() + packet.padding_size(), header);
1606 }
1607}
